Variables

HANDLE g_DeviceHandle
 Holds the global handle of device which is used to send the request to the kernel by IOCTL, this handle is not used for IRP Pending of message tracing this handle is used in KD VMM.
 

Detailed Description

The hyperdbg command interpreter and driver connector.

◆ CommandAttach()

VOID CommandAttach ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,
string  Command 
)

.attach command handler

Parameters
SplittedCommand
Command
Returns
VOID
45{
46 UINT64 TargetPid = 0;
47 BOOLEAN NextIsPid = FALSE;
48
49 //
50 // Disable user-mode debugger in this version
51 //
52#if ActivateUserModeDebugger == FALSE
53
54 if (!g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebugger)
55 {
56 ShowMessages("the user-mode debugger in VMI Mode is still in the beta version and not stable. "
57 "we decided to exclude it from this release and release it in future versions. "
58 "if you want to test the user-mode debugger in VMI Mode, you should build "
59 "HyperDbg with special instructions. But attaching/switching to other processes\n"
60 "are fully supported in the Debugger Mode.\n"
61 "(it's not recommended to use it in VMI Mode yet!)\n");
62 return;
63 }
64
65#endif // !ActivateUserModeDebugger
66
67 //
68 // It's a attach to a target PID
69 //
70 if (SplittedCommand.size() >= 4)
71 {
72 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.attach'\n\n");
73 CommandAttachHelp();
74 return;
75 }
76
77 //
78 // .attach and .detach commands are only supported in VMI Mode
79 //
80 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
81 {
82 ShowMessages("err, '.attach', and '.detach' commands are only usable "
83 "in VMI Mode, you can use the '.process', or the '.thread' "
84 "in Debugger Mode\n");
85 return;
86 }
87
88 for (auto item : SplittedCommand)
89 {
90 //
91 // Find out whether the user enters pid or not
92 //
93 if (NextIsPid)
94 {
95 NextIsPid = FALSE;
96
97 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(item, &TargetPid))
98 {
99 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for process id\n\n");
100 CommandAttachHelp();
101 return;
102 }
103 }
104 else if (!item.compare("pid"))
105 {
106 //
107 // next item is a pid for the process
108 //
109 NextIsPid = TRUE;
110 }
111 }
112
113 //
114 // Check if the process id is empty or not
115 //
116 if (TargetPid == 0)
117 {
118 ShowMessages("please specify a hex value for process id\n\n");
119 CommandAttachHelp();
120 return;
121 }
122
123 //
124 // Perform attach to target process
125 //
126 UdAttachToProcess(TargetPid, NULL, NULL);
127}

◆ CommandBc()

VOID CommandBc ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,
string  Command 
)

handler of bc command

Parameters
SplittedCommand
Command
Returns
VOID
45{
46 UINT64 BreakpointId;
47 DEBUGGEE_BP_LIST_OR_MODIFY_PACKET Request = {0};
48
49 //
50 // Validate the commands
51 //
52 if (SplittedCommand.size() != 2)
53 {
54 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the 'bc'\n\n");
55 CommandBcHelp();
56 return;
57 }
58
59 //
60 // Get the breakpoint id
61 //
62 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(SplittedCommand.at(1), &BreakpointId))
63 {
64 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for breakpoint id\n\n");
65 CommandBcHelp();
66
67 return;
68 }
69
70 //
71 // Check if the remote serial debuggee is paused or not (connected or not)
72 //
73 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
74 {
75 //
76 // Perform clearing breakpoint
77 //
78 Request.Request = DEBUGGEE_BREAKPOINT_MODIFICATION_REQUEST_CLEAR;
79
80 //
81 // Set breakpoint id
82 //
83 Request.BreakpointId = BreakpointId;
84
85 //
86 // Send the request
87 //
88 KdSendListOrModifyPacketToDebuggee(&Request);
89 }
90 else
91 {
92 ShowMessages("err, clearing breakpoints is only valid if you connected to "
93 "a debuggee in debugger-mode\n");
94 }
95}

46{
47 PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_EVENT_DETAIL Event = NULL;

55 UINT32 ActionCustomCodeLength = 0;

58 DEBUGGER_EVENT_PARSING_ERROR_CAUSE EventParsingErrorCause;
59
60 //
61 // Interpret and fill the general event and action fields
62 //
63 //
64 if (!InterpretGeneralEventAndActionsFields(
65 &SplittedCommand,
66 &SplittedCommandCaseSensitive,
67 CPUID_INSTRUCTION_EXECUTION,
68 &Event,
69 &EventLength,
70 &ActionBreakToDebugger,
71 &ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
72 &ActionCustomCode,
73 &ActionCustomCodeLength,
74 &ActionScript,
75 &ActionScriptLength,
76 &EventParsingErrorCause))
77 {
78 return;
79 }
80
81 //
82 // Interpret command specific details (if any), of CPUID EAX index
83 //
84 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
85 {
86 if (!Section.compare("!cpuid"))
87 {
88 continue;
89 }
90 else if (!GetEax)
91 {
92 //
93 // It's probably an msr
94 //
95 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &SpecialTarget))
96 {
97 //
98 // Unkonwn parameter
99 //
100 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
101 CommandCpuidHelp();
102
103 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
104 return;
105 }
106 else
107 {
108 //
109 // An special EAX is set
110 //
111 GetEax = TRUE;
112 }
113 }
114 else
115 {
116 //
117 // Unkonwn parameter
118 //
119 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
120 CommandCpuidHelp();
121
122 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
123 return;
124 }
125 }
126
127 //
128 // Set the target EAX (if not specific then it means all msrs)
129 //
130 Event->OptionalParam1 = GetEax;
131
132 if (GetEax)
133 {
134 Event->OptionalParam2 = SpecialTarget;
135 }
136
137 //
138 // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
139 //
140 if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
141 {
142 //
143 // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
144 // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
145 // already freed the Event and string buffers
146 //
147
148 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
149 return;
150 }
151
152 //
153 // Add the event to the kernel
154 //
155 if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
156 ActionBreakToDebugger,
157 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
158 ActionCustomCode,
159 ActionCustomCodeLength,
160 ActionScript,
161 ActionScriptLength))
162 {
163 //
164 // There was an error
165 //
166 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
167 return;
168 }
169}

81 &ActionScript,
82 &ActionScriptLength,
83 &EventParsingErrorCause))
84 {
85 return;
86 }
87
88 //
89 // Interpret command specific details (if any)
90 //
91 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
92 {
93 if (!Section.compare("!crwrite"))
94 {
95 continue;
96 }
97 else if (!GetRegister)
98 {
99 //
100 // It's probably a CR
101 //
102 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &TargetRegister))
103 {
104 //
105 // Unkonwn parameter
106 //
107 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
108 CommandCrwriteHelp();
109
110 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
111 return;
112 }
113 else
114 {
115 GetRegister = TRUE;
116 }
117 }
118 else if (!GetMask)
119 {
120 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &MaskRegister))
121 {
122 //
123 // Unkonwn parameter
124 //
125 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
126 CommandCrwriteHelp();
127
128 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
129 return;
130 }
131 else
132 {
133 GetMask = TRUE;
134 }
135 }
136 else
137 {
138 //
139 // Unkonwn parameter
140 //
141 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
142 CommandCrwriteHelp();
143
144 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
145 return;
146 }
147 }
148
149 if (TargetRegister != VMX_EXIT_QUALIFICATION_REGISTER_CR0 && TargetRegister != VMX_EXIT_QUALIFICATION_REGISTER_CR4)
150 {
151 ShowMessages("please choose either 0 for cr0 or 4 for cr4\n");
152 CommandCrwriteHelp();
153
154 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
155 return;
156 }
157
158 //
159 // Set the target control register
160 //
161 Event->OptionalParam1 = TargetRegister;
162
163 //
164 // Set the mask to filter control register bits
165 //
166 Event->OptionalParam2 = MaskRegister;
167
168 //
169 // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
170 //
171 if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
172 {
173 //
174 // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
175 // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
176 // already freed the Event and string buffers
177 //
178 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
179 return;
180 }
181
182 //
183 // Add the event to the kernel
184 //
185 if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
186 ActionBreakToDebugger,
187 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
188 ActionCustomCode,
189 ActionCustomCodeLength,
190 ActionScript,
191 ActionScriptLength))
192 {
193 //
194 // There was an error
195 //
196 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
197 return;
198 }
199}

94 {
95 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive++;
96
97 if (!Section.compare(SplittedCommand.at(0)))
98 {
99 if (!Section.compare("!eb"))
100 {
101 EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
102 EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_BYTE;
103 }
104 else if (!Section.compare("!ed"))
105 {
106 EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
107 EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_DWORD;
108 }
109 else if (!Section.compare("!eq"))
110 {
111 EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
112 EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_QWORD;
113 }
114 else if (!Section.compare("eb"))
115 {
116 EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
117 EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_BYTE;
118 }
119 else if (!Section.compare("ed"))
120 {
121 EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
122 EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_DWORD;
123 }
124 else if (!Section.compare("eq"))
125 {
126 EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
127 EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_QWORD;
128 }
129 else
130 {
131 //
132 // What's this? :(
133 //
134 ShowMessages("unknown error happened !\n\n");
135 CommandEditMemoryHelp();
136 return;
137 }
138
139 continue;
140 }
141
142 if (NextIsProcId)
143 {
144 //
145 // It's a process id
146 //
147 NextIsProcId = FALSE;
148
149 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &ProcId))
150 {
151 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex prcoess id\n\n");
152 CommandEditMemoryHelp();
153 return;
154 }
155 else
156 {
157 //
158 // Means that the proc id is set, next we should read value
159 //
160 continue;
161 }
162 }
163
164 //
165 // Check if it's a process id or not
166 //
167 if (!SetProcId && !Section.compare("pid"))
168 {
169 NextIsProcId = TRUE;
170 continue;
171 }
172
173 if (!SetAddress)
174 {
175 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1),
176 &Address))
177 {
178 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
179 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
180 CommandEditMemoryHelp();
181 return;
182 }
183 else
184 {
185 //
186 // Means that the address is set, next we should read value
187 //
188 SetAddress = TRUE;
189 continue;
190 }
191 }
192
193 if (SetAddress)
194 {
195 //
196 // Remove the hex notations
197 //
198 if (Section.rfind("0x", 0) == 0 || Section.rfind("0X", 0) == 0 ||
199 Section.rfind("\\x", 0) == 0 || Section.rfind("\\X", 0) == 0)
200 {
201 Section = Section.erase(0, 2);
202 }
203 else if (Section.rfind('x', 0) == 0 || Section.rfind('X', 0) == 0)
204 {
205 Section = Section.erase(0, 1);
206 }
207 Section.erase(remove(Section.begin(), Section.end(), '`'), Section.end());
208
209 //
210 // Check if the value is valid based on byte counts
211 //
212 if (EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize == EDIT_BYTE && Section.size() >= 3)
213 {
214 ShowMessages("please specify a byte (hex) value for 'eb' or '!eb'\n\n");
215 return;
216 }
217 if (EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize == EDIT_DWORD && Section.size() >= 9)
218 {
219 ShowMessages(
220 "please specify a dword (hex) value for 'ed' or '!ed'\n\n");
221 return;
222 }
223 if (EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize == EDIT_QWORD && Section.size() >= 17)
224 {
225 ShowMessages(
226 "please specify a qword (hex) value for 'eq' or '!eq'\n\n");
227 return;
228 }
229
230 //
231 // Qword is checked by the following function, no need to double
232 // check it above.
233 //
234
235 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &Value))
236 {
237 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to change the memory "
238 "content\n\n");
239 CommandEditMemoryHelp();
240 return;
241 }
242 else
243 {
244 //
245 // Add it to the list
246 //
247
248 ValuesToEdit.push_back(Value);
249
250 //
251 // Keep track of values to modify
252 //
253 CountOfValues++;
254
255 if (!SetValue)
256 {
257 //
258 // At least on value is there
259 //
260 SetValue = TRUE;
261 }
262 continue;
263 }
264 }
265 }
266
267 //
268 // Check to prevent using process id in e* commands
269 //
270 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee && ProcId != 0)
271 {
272 ShowMessages(ASSERT_MESSAGE_CANNOT_SPECIFY_PID);
273 return;
274 }
275
276 if (ProcId == 0)
277 {
278 ProcId = GetCurrentProcessId();
279 }
280
281 //
282 // Fill the structure
283 //
284 EditMemoryRequest.ProcessId = ProcId;
285 EditMemoryRequest.Address = Address;
286 EditMemoryRequest.CountOf64Chunks = CountOfValues;
287
288 //
289 // Check if address and value are set or not
290 //
291 if (!SetAddress)
292 {
293 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex address\n\n");
294 CommandEditMemoryHelp();
295 return;
296 }
297 if (!SetValue)
298 {
299 ShowMessages(
300 "please specify a correct hex value as the content to edit\n\n");
301 CommandEditMemoryHelp();
302 return;
303 }
304 if (NextIsProcId)
305 {
306 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value as the process id\n\n");
307 CommandEditMemoryHelp();
308 return;
309 }
310
311 //
312 // Now it's time to put everything together in one structure
313 //
314 FinalSize = (CountOfValues * sizeof(UINT64)) + SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY;
315
316 //
317 // Set the size
318 //
319 EditMemoryRequest.FinalStructureSize = FinalSize;
320
321 //
322 // Allocate structure + buffer
323 //
324 FinalBuffer = (UINT64 *)malloc(FinalSize);
325
326 if (!FinalBuffer)
327 {
328 ShowMessages("unable to allocate memory\n\n");
329 return;
330 }
331
332 //
333 // Zero the buffer
334 //
335 ZeroMemory(FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
336
337 //
338 // Copy the structure on top of the allocated buffer
339 //
340 memcpy(FinalBuffer, &EditMemoryRequest, SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY);
341
342 //
343 // Put the values in 64 bit structures
344 //
345 std::copy(ValuesToEdit.begin(), ValuesToEdit.end(), (UINT64 *)((UINT64)FinalBuffer + SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY));
346
347 //
348 // send the request
349 //
350 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
351 {
352 KdSendEditMemoryPacketToDebuggee((DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY *)FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
353 return;
354 }
355
356 //
357 // It's on VMI mode
358 //
359 AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
360
361 Status = DeviceIoControl(
362 g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
363 IOCTL_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY, // IO Control code
364 FinalBuffer, // Input Buffer to driver.
365 FinalSize, // Input buffer length
366 &EditMemoryRequest, // Output Buffer from driver.
367 SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY, // Length of output buffer in bytes.
368 NULL, // Bytes placed in buffer.
369 NULL // synchronous call
370 );
371
372 if (!Status)
373 {
374 free(FinalBuffer);
375 ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code 0x%x\n", GetLastError());
376 return;
377 }
378
379 if (EditMemoryRequest.Result == DEBUGGER_OPERATION_WAS_SUCCESSFUL)
380 {
381 //
382 // Was successful, nothing to do
383 //
384 }
385 else if (
386 EditMemoryRequest.Result ==
387 DEBUGGER_ERROR_EDIT_MEMORY_STATUS_INVALID_ADDRESS_BASED_ON_CURRENT_PROCESS)
388 {
389 ShowMessages("err, the address is invalid in system process layout\n");
390 }
391 else if (
392 EditMemoryRequest.Result ==
393 DEBUGGER_ERROR_EDIT_MEMORY_STATUS_INVALID_ADDRESS_BASED_ON_OTHER_PROCESS)
394 {
395 ShowMessages("err, the address is invalid based on your specific process id\n");
396 }
397 else if (EditMemoryRequest.Result ==
398 DEBUGGER_ERROR_EDIT_MEMORY_STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER)
399 {
400 ShowMessages("invalid parameter\n");
401 }
402 else
403 {
404 ShowErrorMessage(EditMemoryRequest.Result);
405 }
406
407 //
408 // Free the malloc buffer
409 //
410 free(FinalBuffer);
411}
DEBUGGER_ERROR_EDIT_MEMORY_STATUS_INVALID_ADDRESS_BASED_ON_OTHER_PROCESS
#define DEBUGGER_ERROR_EDIT_MEMORY_STATUS_INVALID_ADDRESS_BASED_ON_OTHER_PROCESS

61
62 if (SplittedCommand.size() < 2)
63 {
64 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!epthook'\n");
65 CommandEptHookHelp();
66 return;
67 }
68
69 //
70 // Interpret and fill the general event and action fields
71 //
72 if (!InterpretGeneralEventAndActionsFields(
73 &SplittedCommand,
74 &SplittedCommandCaseSensitive,
75 HIDDEN_HOOK_EXEC_CC,
76 &Event,
77 &EventLength,
78 &ActionBreakToDebugger,
79 &ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
80 &ActionCustomCode,
81 &ActionCustomCodeLength,
82 &ActionScript,

84 &EventParsingErrorCause))
85 {
86 return;
87 }
88
89 //
90 // Interpret command specific details (if any)
91 //
92 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
93 {
94 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive++;
95

97 {
98 continue;
99 }

112 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",

114 CommandEptHookHelp();
115
116 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
117 return;
118 }
119 else
120 {
121 GetAddress = TRUE;
122 }
123 }
124 else
125 {
126 //
127 // Unkonwn parameter
128 //
129 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
130 CommandEptHookHelp();
131
132 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
133 return;
134 }
135 }
136 if (OptionalParam1 == 0)
137 {
138 ShowMessages("please choose an address to put the hidden breakpoint on it\n");
139
140 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
141 return;
142 }
143
144 //
145 // Set the optional parameters
146 //
147 Event->OptionalParam1 = OptionalParam1;
148
149 //
150 // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
151 //
152 if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
153 {
154 //
155 // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
156 // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
157 // already freed the Event and string buffers
158 //
159
160 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
161 return;
162 }
163
164 //
165 // Add the event to the kernel
166 //
167 if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
168 ActionBreakToDebugger,
169 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
170 ActionCustomCode,
171 ActionCustomCodeLength,
172 ActionScript,
173 ActionScriptLength))
174 {
175 //
176 // There was an error
177 //
178
179 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
180 return;
181 }
182}

76 CommandEventsHelp();

78 }
79
80 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 1)
81 {
82 if (!g_EventTraceInitialized)
83 {
84 ShowMessages("no active/disabled events \n");
85 return;
86 }
87
88 CommandEventsShowEvents();
89
90 //
91 // No need to continue any further
92 //
93 return;
94 }
95
96 //
97 // Validate second argument as it's not just a simple
98 // events without any parameter
99 //
100 if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("e"))
101 {
102 RequestedAction = DEBUGGER_MODIFY_EVENTS_ENABLE;
103 }
104 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("d"))
105 {
106 RequestedAction = DEBUGGER_MODIFY_EVENTS_DISABLE;
107 }
108 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("c"))
109 {
110 RequestedAction = DEBUGGER_MODIFY_EVENTS_CLEAR;
111 }
112 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("sc"))
113 {
114 if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("on"))
115 {
116 KdSendShortCircuitingEventToDebuggee(TRUE);
117 }
118 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("off"))
119 {
120 KdSendShortCircuitingEventToDebuggee(FALSE);
121 }
122 else
123 {
124 ShowMessages(
125 "please specify a correct 'on' or 'off' state for the short-circuiting state\n\n");
126 CommandEventsHelp();
127 return;
128 }
129
130 //
131 // No need to further continue
132 //
133 return;
134 }
135 else
136 {
137 //
138 // unknown second command
139 //
140 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '%s'\n\n", SplittedCommand.at(0).c_str());
141 CommandEventsHelp();
142 return;
143 }
144
145 //
146 // Validate third argument as it's not just a simple
147 // events without any parameter
148 //
149 if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("all"))
150 {
151 RequestedTag = DEBUGGER_MODIFY_EVENTS_APPLY_TO_ALL_TAG;
152 }
153 else if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(SplittedCommand.at(2), &RequestedTag))
154 {
155 ShowMessages(
156 "please specify a correct hex value for tag id (event number)\n\n");
157 CommandEventsHelp();
158 return;
159 }
160
161 //
162 // Send the request to the kernel, we add it to a constant
163 // that's because we want start tags from that constant
164 //
165 if (RequestedTag != DEBUGGER_MODIFY_EVENTS_APPLY_TO_ALL_TAG)
166 {
167 RequestedTag = RequestedTag + DebuggerEventTagStartSeed;
168 }
169
170 //
171 // Perform event related tasks
172 //
173 CommandEventsModifyAndQueryEvents(RequestedTag, RequestedAction);
174}

124 return;
125 }

133 //

61{
62 BOOLEAN Status;
63 ULONG ReturnedLength;
64 UINT64 TargetPid;
65 BOOLEAN TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName;
66 DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE HideRequest = {0};

69
70 if (SplittedCommand.size() <= 2 && SplittedCommand.size() != 1)
71 {
72 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!hide'\n\n");
73 CommandHideHelp();
74 return;
75 }
76
77 //
78 // Find out whether the user enters pid or name
79 //
80 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 1)
81 {
82 if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
83 {
84 TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName = TRUE;
85 TargetPid = g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId;
86 }
87 else
88 {
89 //
90 // There is no user-debugging process
91 //

93 "please explicitly specify the process id or process name\n");
94 return;
95 }
96 }
97 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("pid"))
98 {
99 TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName = TRUE;
100
101 //
102 // Check for the user to not add extra arguments
103 //

105 {
106 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!hide'\n\n");
107 CommandHideHelp();
108 return;
109 }
110
111 //
112 // It's just a pid for the process
113 //
114 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(SplittedCommand.at(2), &TargetPid))
115 {
116 ShowMessages("incorrect process id\n\n");
117 return;
118 }
119 }
120 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("name"))
121 {
122 TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName = FALSE;
123

125 // Trim the command
126 //
127 Trim(Command);
128
129 //
130 // Remove !hide from it
131 //
132 Command.erase(0, 5);
133
134 //
135 // remove name + space
136 //
137 Command.erase(0, 4 + 1);
138
139 //
140 // Trim it again
141 //
142 Trim(Command);
143 }
144 else
145 {
146 //
147 // Invalid argument for the second parameter to the command
148 //
149 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!hide'\n\n");
150 CommandHideHelp();
151 return;
152 }
153
154 //
155 // Check if the user used !measure or not
156 //
157 if (!g_TransparentResultsMeasured || !g_CpuidAverage ||
158 !g_CpuidStandardDeviation || !g_CpuidMedian)
159 {
160 ShowMessages("the average, median and standard deviation is not measured. "
161 "Did you use '!measure' command?\n");
162 return;
163 }
164
165 //
166 // Check if debugger is loaded or not
167 //
168 AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
169
170 //
171 // We wanna hide the debugger and make transparent vm-exits
172 //
173 HideRequest.IsHide = TRUE;
174
175 //
176 // Set the measured times cpuid
177 //
178 HideRequest.CpuidAverage = g_CpuidAverage;
179 HideRequest.CpuidMedian = g_CpuidMedian;
180 HideRequest.CpuidStandardDeviation = g_CpuidStandardDeviation;
181
182 //
183 // Set the measured times rdtsc/p
184 //
185 HideRequest.RdtscAverage = g_RdtscAverage;
186 HideRequest.RdtscMedian = g_RdtscMedian;
187 HideRequest.RdtscStandardDeviation = g_RdtscStandardDeviation;
188
189 HideRequest.TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName =
190 TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName;
191
192 if (TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName)
193 {
194 //
195 // It's a process id
196 //
197 HideRequest.ProcId = TargetPid;
198
199 RequestBufferSize = sizeof(DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE);
200 }
201 else
202 {
203 //
204 // It's a process name
205 //
206 HideRequest.LengthOfProcessName = Command.size() + 1;
207 RequestBufferSize = sizeof(DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE) +
208 Command.size() + 1;
209 }
210
211 //
212 // Allocate the requested buffer
213 //
214 FinalRequestBuffer =
215 (PDEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE)malloc(RequestBufferSize);
216
217 //
218 // Zero the memory
219 //
220 RtlZeroMemory(FinalRequestBuffer, RequestBufferSize);
221
222 //
223 // Copy the buffer on the top of the final buffer
224 // to send the kernel
225 //
226 memcpy(FinalRequestBuffer, &HideRequest, sizeof(DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE));
227
228 //
229 // If it's a name then we should add it to the end of the buffer
230 //
231 memcpy(((UINT64 *)((UINT64)FinalRequestBuffer +
232 sizeof(DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE))),
233 Command.c_str(),
234 Command.size());
235
236 //
237 // Send the request to the kernel
238 //
239
240 Status = DeviceIoControl(
241 g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
242 IOCTL_DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_UNHIDE_TO_TRANSPARENT_THE_DEBUGGER, // IO Control
243 // code
244 FinalRequestBuffer, // Input Buffer to driver.
245 RequestBufferSize, // Input buffer length
246 FinalRequestBuffer, // Output Buffer from driver.
247 SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE, // Length of output
248 // buffer in bytes.
249 &ReturnedLength, // Bytes placed in buffer.
250 NULL // synchronous call
251 );
252
253 if (!Status)
254 {
255 ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code 0x%x\n", GetLastError());
256 free(FinalRequestBuffer);
257 return;
258 }
259
260 if (FinalRequestBuffer->KernelStatus == DEBUGGER_OPERATION_WAS_SUCCESSFUL)
261 {
262 ShowMessages("transparent debugging successfully enabled :)\n");
263 }
264 else if (FinalRequestBuffer->KernelStatus ==
265 DEBUGGER_ERROR_UNABLE_TO_HIDE_OR_UNHIDE_DEBUGGER)
266 {
267 ShowMessages("unable to hide the debugger (transparent-debugging) :(\n");
268 free(FinalRequestBuffer);
269 return;
270 }
271 else
272 {
273 ShowMessages("unknown error occurred :(\n");
274 free(FinalRequestBuffer);
275 return;
276 }
277
278 //
279 // free the buffer
280 //
281 free(FinalRequestBuffer);
282}

147 // We're not instrumenting instructions anymore
148 //
149 g_IsInstrumentingInstructions = FALSE;
150 }
151 else
152 {
153 ShowMessages("err, stepping (i) is not valid in the current context, you "
154 "should connect to a debuggee\n");
155 }

VOID CommandInterrupt ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,
string  Command 
)

!interrupt command handler

VOID
46{
47 PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_EVENT_DETAIL Event = NULL;
48 PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionBreakToDebugger = NULL;
49 PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionCustomCode = NULL;
50 PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionScript = NULL;
51 UINT32 EventLength;
52 UINT32 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength = 0;
53 UINT32 ActionCustomCodeLength = 0;
54 UINT32 ActionScriptLength = 0;
55 UINT64 SpecialTarget = 0;
56 BOOLEAN GetEntry = FALSE;
57 vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
58 DEBUGGER_EVENT_PARSING_ERROR_CAUSE EventParsingErrorCause;
59
60 //
61 // Interpret and fill the general event and action fields
62 //
63 //
64 if (!InterpretGeneralEventAndActionsFields(
65 &SplittedCommand,
66 &SplittedCommandCaseSensitive,
67 EXTERNAL_INTERRUPT_OCCURRED,
68 &Event,
69 &EventLength,
70 &ActionBreakToDebugger,
71 &ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
72 &ActionCustomCode,
73 &ActionCustomCodeLength,
74 &ActionScript,
75 &ActionScriptLength,
76 &EventParsingErrorCause))
77 {
78 return;
79 }
80
81 //
82 // Interpret command specific details (if any)
83 //
84 //
85 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
86 {
87 if (!Section.compare("!interrupt"))
88 {
89 continue;
90 }
91 else if (!GetEntry)
92 {
93 //
94 // It's probably an index
95 //
96 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &SpecialTarget))
97 {
98 //
99 // Unkonwn parameter
100 //
101 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
102 CommandInterruptHelp();
103
104 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
105 return;
106 }
107 else
108 {
109 //
110 // Check if entry is valid or not
111 //
112 if (!(SpecialTarget >= 32 && SpecialTarget <= 0xff))
113 {
114 //
115 // Entry is invalid (this command is designed for just entries
116 // between 32 to 255)
117 //
118 ShowMessages("the entry should be between 0x20 to 0xFF or the "
119 "entries between 32 to 255\n\n");
120 CommandInterruptHelp();
121
122 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
123 return;
124 }
125 GetEntry = TRUE;
126 }
127 }
128 else
129 {
130 //
131 // Unkonwn parameter
132 //
133 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
134 CommandInterruptHelp();
135
136 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
137 return;
138 }
139 }
140
141 if (SpecialTarget == 0)
142 {
143 //
144 // The user didn't set the target interrupt, even though it's possible to
145 // get all interrupts but it makes the system not resposive so it's wrong
146 // to trigger event on all interrupts and we're not going to support it
147 //
148 ShowMessages("please specify an interrupt index to monitor, HyperDbg "
149 "doesn't support to trigger events on all interrupts because "
150 "it's not reasonable and make the system unresponsive\n");
151 CommandInterruptHelp();
152
153 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
154 return;
155 }
156
157 //
158 // Set the target interrupt
159 //
160 Event->OptionalParam1 = SpecialTarget;
161
162 //
163 // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
164 //
165 if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
166 {
167 //
168 // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
169 // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
170 // already freed the Event and string buffers
171 //
172
173 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
174 return;
175 }
176
177 //
178 // Add the event to the kernel
179 //
180 if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
181 ActionBreakToDebugger,
182 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
183 ActionCustomCode,
184 ActionCustomCodeLength,
185 ActionScript,
186 ActionScriptLength))
187 {
188 //
189 // There was an error
190 //
191
192 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
193 return;
194 }
195}

56{
57 UINT64 BaseAddress = NULL; // Null base address means current RSP register
58 UINT32 Length = 0x100; // Default length
59 vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
60 UINT32 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive = 0;
61 BOOLEAN IsFirstCommand = TRUE;
62 BOOLEAN IsNextBase = FALSE;
63 BOOLEAN IsNextLength = FALSE;
64
65 string FirstCommand = SplittedCommand.front();
66
67 if (SplittedCommand.size() >= 6)
68 {
69 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '%s'\n\n", FirstCommand.c_str());
70 CommandKHelp();
71 return;
72 }
73
74 if (!g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
75 {
76 ShowMessages("err, tracing callstack is not possible when you're not "
77 "connected to a debuggee\n");
78 return;
79 }
80
81 //
82 // Set the default length
83 //
84 if (g_IsRunningInstruction32Bit)
85 {
86 Length = 0x100;
87 }
88 else
89 {
90 Length = 0x200;
91 }
92
93 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
94 {
95 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive++;
96
97 if (IsFirstCommand)
98 {
99 IsFirstCommand = FALSE;
100 continue;
101 }
102 if (IsNextBase == TRUE)
103 {
104 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1),
105 &BaseAddress))
106 {
107 //
108 // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
109 //
110 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
111 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
112 return;
113 }
114
115 IsNextBase = FALSE;
116 continue;
117 }
118
119 if (IsNextLength == TRUE)
120 {
121 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &Length))
122 {
123 ShowMessages("err, you should enter a valid length\n\n");
124 return;
125 }
126 IsNextLength = FALSE;
127 continue;
128 }
129
130 if (!Section.compare("l"))
131 {
132 IsNextLength = TRUE;
133 continue;
134 }
135
136 if (!Section.compare("base"))
137 {
138 IsNextBase = TRUE;
139 continue;
140 }
141
142 //
143 // User inserts unexpected input
144 //
145 ShowMessages("err, incorrect use of the '%s' command\n\n",
146 FirstCommand.c_str());
147 CommandKHelp();
148
149 return;
150 }
151
152 if (IsNextLength || IsNextBase)
153 {
154 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '%s' command\n\n", FirstCommand.c_str());
155 CommandKHelp();
156 return;
157 }
158
159 //
160 // Send callstack request
161 //
162
163 if (!FirstCommand.compare("k"))
164 {
165 KdSendCallStackPacketToDebuggee(BaseAddress,
166 Length,
167 DEBUGGER_CALLSTACK_DISPLAY_METHOD_WITHOUT_PARAMS,
168 g_IsRunningInstruction32Bit);
169 }
170 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("kq"))
171 {
172 KdSendCallStackPacketToDebuggee(BaseAddress,
173 Length,
174 DEBUGGER_CALLSTACK_DISPLAY_METHOD_WITH_PARAMS,
175 FALSE);
176 }
177 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("kd"))
178 {
179 KdSendCallStackPacketToDebuggee(BaseAddress,
180 Length,
181 DEBUGGER_CALLSTACK_DISPLAY_METHOD_WITH_PARAMS,
182 TRUE);
183 }
184}

54{

◆ CommandLm()

VOID CommandLm ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,

handle lm command

Parameters
SplittedCommand
Command
Returns
VOID
386{
387 BOOLEAN SetPid = FALSE;
388 BOOLEAN SetSearchFilter = FALSE;
389 BOOLEAN SearchStringEntered = FALSE;
390 BOOLEAN OnlyShowKernelModules = FALSE;
391 BOOLEAN OnlyShowUserModules = FALSE;
392 UINT32 TargetPid = NULL;
393 char Search[MAX_PATH] = {0};
394 char * SearchString = NULL;
395
396 //
397 // Interpret command specific details (if any)
398 //
399 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
400 {
401 if (!Section.compare("lm"))
402 {
403 continue;
404 }
405 else if (!Section.compare("pid") && !SetPid)
406 {
407 SetPid = TRUE;
408 }
409 else if (!Section.compare("m") && !SetSearchFilter)
410 {
411 SetSearchFilter = TRUE;
412 }
413 else if (SetPid)
414 {
415 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &TargetPid))
416 {
417 //
418 // couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
419 //
420 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
421 Section.c_str());
422 CommandLmHelp();
423 return;
424 }
425 SetPid = FALSE;
426 }
427 else if (SetSearchFilter)
428 {
429 if (Section.length() >= MAX_PATH)
430 {
431 ShowMessages("err, string is too large for search, please enter "
432 "smaller string\n");
433
434 return;
435 }
436
437 SearchStringEntered = TRUE;
438 strcpy(Search, Section.c_str());
439
440 SetSearchFilter = FALSE;
441 }
442 else if (!Section.compare("km"))
443 {
444 if (OnlyShowUserModules)
445 {
446 ShowMessages("err, you cannot use both 'um', and 'km', by default "
447 "HyperDbg shows both user-mode and kernel-mode modules\n");
448 return;
449 }
450
451 OnlyShowKernelModules = TRUE;
452 }
453 else if (!Section.compare("um"))
454 {
455 if (OnlyShowKernelModules)
456 {
457 ShowMessages("err, you cannot use both 'um', and 'km', by default "
458 "HyperDbg shows both user-mode and kernel-mode modules\n");
459 return;
460 }
461
462 OnlyShowUserModules = TRUE;
463 }
464 else
465 {
466 //
467 // Unknown parameter
468 //
469 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
470 Section.c_str());
471 CommandLmHelp();
472 return;
473 }
474 }
475
476 if (SetPid)
477 {
478 ShowMessages("err, please enter a valid process id in hex format, "
479 "or if you want to use it in decimal format, add '0n' "
480 "prefix to the number\n");
481 return;
482 }
483
484 if (SetSearchFilter)
485 {
486 ShowMessages("err, please enter a valid string to search in modules\n");
487 return;
488 }
489
490 //
491 // Check if we have string to search
492 //
493 if (SearchStringEntered)
494 {
495 SearchString = Search;
496 }
497
498 //
499 // Show user mode modules
500 //
501 if (!OnlyShowKernelModules)
502 {
503 if (TargetPid != NULL)
504 {
505 CommandLmShowUserModeModule(TargetPid, SearchString);
506 }
507 else if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
508 {
509 CommandLmShowUserModeModule(g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId, SearchString);
510 }
511 else
512 {
513 CommandLmShowUserModeModule(GetCurrentProcessId(), SearchString);
514 }
515 }
516
517 //
518 // Show kernel mode modules
519 //
520 if (!OnlyShowUserModules)
521 {
522 if (!OnlyShowKernelModules)
523 {
524 ShowMessages("\n==============================================================================\n\n");
525 }
526
527 CommandLmShowKernelModeModule(SearchString);

54{
55 BOOLEAN DefaultMode = FALSE;
56
57 if (SplittedCommand.size() >= 3)
58 {
59 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!measure'\n\n");
60 CommandMeasureHelp();
61 return;
62 }
63
64 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 2 && SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("default"))
65 {
66 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!measure'\n\n");
67 CommandMeasureHelp();
68 return;
69 }
70 else if (SplittedCommand.size() == 2 &&
71 !SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("default"))
72 {
73 DefaultMode = TRUE;
74 }
75
76 //
77 // Check if debugger is loaded or not
78 //
79 if (g_DeviceHandle && !DefaultMode)
80 {
81 ShowMessages(
82 "Debugger is loaded and your machine is already in a hypervisor, you "
83 "should measure the times before 'load'-ing the debugger, please "
84 "'unload' the debugger and use '!measure' again or use '!measure "
85 "default' to use hardcoded measurements\n");
86 return;
87 }
88
89 if (!DefaultMode)
90 {
91 if (TransparentModeCheckHypervisorPresence(
92 &g_CpuidAverage,
93 &g_CpuidStandardDeviation,
94 &g_CpuidMedian))
95 {
96 ShowMessages(
97 "we detected that there is a hypervisor, on your system, it "
98 "leads to wrong measurement results for our transparent-mode, please "
99 "make sure that you're not in a hypervisor then measure the result "
100 "again; otherwise the transparent-mode will not work but you can use "
101 "'!measure default' to use the hardcoded measurements !\n\n");
102
103 return;
104 }
105
106 if (TransparentModeCheckRdtscpVmexit(
107 &g_RdtscAverage,
108 &g_RdtscStandardDeviation,
109 &g_RdtscMedian))
110 {
111 ShowMessages(
112 "we detected that there is a hypervisor, on your system, it "
113 "leads to wrong measurement results for our transparent-mode, please "
114 "make sure that you're not in a hypervisor then measure the result "
115 "again; otherwise the transparent-mode will not work but you can use "
116 "'!measure default' to use the hardcoded measurements !\n\n");
117
118 return;
119 }
120 }
121 else
122 {
123 //
124 // It's a default mode
125 //
126
127 //
128 // Default values for cpuid
129 //
130 g_CpuidAverage = 0x5f;
131 g_CpuidStandardDeviation = 0x10;
132 g_CpuidMedian = 0x5f;
133
134 //
135 // Default values for rdtsc/p
136 //
137 g_RdtscAverage = 0x16;
138 g_RdtscStandardDeviation = 0x5;
139 g_RdtscMedian = 0x16;
140 }
141
142 ShowMessages("the measurements were successful\nyou can use the '!hide' command now\n");
143
144 //
145 // Indicate that the measurements was successful
146 //
147 g_TransparentResultsMeasured = TRUE;
148}

◆ CommandMonitor()

VOID CommandMonitor ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,
string  Command 
)

!monitor command handler

Parameters
SplittedCommand
Command
Returns
VOID
48{
49 PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_EVENT_DETAIL Event = NULL;
50 PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionBreakToDebugger = NULL;
51 PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionCustomCode = NULL;
52 PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionScript = NULL;
53 UINT32 EventLength;
54 UINT32 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength = 0;
55 UINT32 ActionCustomCodeLength = 0;
56 UINT32 ActionScriptLength = 0;
57 UINT64 TargetAddress;
58 UINT64 OptionalParam1 = 0; // Set the 'from' target address
59 UINT64 OptionalParam2 = 0; // Set the 'to' target address
60 BOOLEAN SetFrom = FALSE;
61 BOOLEAN SetTo = FALSE;
62 BOOLEAN SetMode = FALSE;
63 vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
64 UINT32 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive = 0;
65 DEBUGGER_EVENT_PARSING_ERROR_CAUSE EventParsingErrorCause;
66
67 if (SplittedCommand.size() < 4)
68 {
69 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!monitor'\n");
70 CommandMonitorHelp();
71 return;
72 }
73
74 //
75 // Interpret and fill the general event and action fields
76 //
77 // We use HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE here but it might be changed to
78 // HIDDEN_HOOK_READ or HIDDEN_HOOK_WRITE or other events it is because
79 // we are not sure what kind event the user need
80 //
81 if (!InterpretGeneralEventAndActionsFields(
82 &SplittedCommand,
83 &SplittedCommandCaseSensitive,
84 HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE_AND_EXECUTE,
85 &Event,
86 &EventLength,
87 &ActionBreakToDebugger,
88 &ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
89 &ActionCustomCode,
90 &ActionCustomCodeLength,
91 &ActionScript,
92 &ActionScriptLength,
93 &EventParsingErrorCause))
94 {
95 return;
96 }
97
98 //
99 // Interpret command specific details (if any)
100 //
101 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
102 {
103 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive++;
104
105 if (!Section.compare("!monitor"))
106 {
107 continue;
108 }
109 else if (!Section.compare("r") && !SetMode)
110 {
111 Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_READ;
112 SetMode = TRUE;
113 }
114 else if (!Section.compare("w") && !SetMode)
115 {
116 Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_WRITE;
117 SetMode = TRUE;
118 }
119 else if (!Section.compare("x") && !SetMode)
120 {
121 Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_EXECUTE;
122 SetMode = TRUE;
123 }
124 else if ((!Section.compare("rw") || !Section.compare("wr")) && !SetMode)
125 {
126 Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE;
127 SetMode = TRUE;
128 }
129 else if ((!Section.compare("rx") || !Section.compare("xr")) &&
130 !SetMode)
131 {
132 Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_EXECUTE;
133 SetMode = TRUE;
134 }
135 else if ((!Section.compare("wx") || !Section.compare("xw")) &&
136 !SetMode)
137 {
138 Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_WRITE_AND_EXECUTE;
139 SetMode = TRUE;
140 }
141 else if ((!Section.compare("rwx") || !Section.compare("rxw") || !Section.compare("wrx") || !Section.compare("wxr") || !Section.compare("xrw") || !Section.compare("xwr")) &&
142 !SetMode)
143 {
144 Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE_AND_EXECUTE;
145 SetMode = TRUE;
146 }
147 else
148 {
149 //
150 // It's probably address
151 //
152 if (!SetFrom)
153 {
154 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(
155 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1),
156 &OptionalParam1))
157 {
158 //
159 // couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
160 //
161 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
162 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
163 CommandMonitorHelp();
164
165 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
166 return;
167 }
168 SetFrom = TRUE;
169 }
170 else if (!SetTo)
171 {
172 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(
173 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1),
174 &OptionalParam2))
175 {
176 //
177 // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
178 //
179 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
180 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
181
182 CommandMonitorHelp();
183
184 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
185 return;
186 }
187 SetTo = TRUE;
188 }
189 else
190 {
191 //
192 // Unkonwn parameter
193 //
194 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
195 CommandMonitorHelp();
196
197 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
198 return;
199 }
200 }
201 }
202
203 //
204 // Check for invalid order of address
205 //
206 if (OptionalParam1 > OptionalParam2)
207 {
208 //
209 // 'from' is greater than 'to'
210 //
211 ShowMessages("please choose the 'from' value first, then choose the 'to' "
212 "value\n");
213
214 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
215 return;
216 }
217
218 //
219 // Check if user set the mode of !monitor or not
220 //
221 if (!SetMode)
222 {
223 ShowMessages("please specify the attribute(s) that you want to monitor (r, w, rw)\n");
224
225 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
226 return;
227 }
228
229 //
230 // Set the optional parameters
231 //
232 Event->OptionalParam1 = OptionalParam1;
233 Event->OptionalParam2 = OptionalParam2;
234
235 //
236 // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
237 //
238 if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
239 {
240 //
241 // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
242 // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
243 // already freed the Event and string buffers
244 //
245
246 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
247 return;
248 }
249
250 //
251 // Add the event to the kernel
252 //
253 if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
254 ActionBreakToDebugger,
255 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
256 ActionCustomCode,
257 ActionCustomCodeLength,
258 ActionScript,
259 ActionScriptLength))
260 {
261 //
262 // There was an error
263 //
264
265 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
266 return;
267 }
268}
HIDDEN_HOOK_WRITE_AND_EXECUTE
@ HIDDEN_HOOK_WRITE_AND_EXECUTE
Definition Events.h:111
HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE
@ HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE
Definition Events.h:109

Definition Events.h:110

HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE_AND_EXECUTE

Definition Events.h:108

@ HIDDEN_HOOK_EXECUTE

103 return;
104 }
105 else
106 {

108 }
109 }
110 else
111 {
112 //
113 // Unkonwn parameter
114 //
115 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
116 CommandMsrreadHelp();
117
118 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
119 return;
120 }
121 }
122
123 //
124 // Set the target msr (if not specific then it means all msrs)
125 //
126 Event->OptionalParam1 = SpecialTarget;
127
128 //
129 // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
130 //
131 if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
132 {
133 //
134 // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
135 // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
136 // already freed the Event and string buffers
137 //
138
139 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
140 return;
141 }
142
143 //
144 // Add the event to the kernel
145 //
146 if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
147 ActionBreakToDebugger,
148 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
149 ActionCustomCode,
150 ActionCustomCodeLength,
151 ActionScript,
152 ActionScriptLength))
153 {
154 //
155 // There was an error
156 //
157
158 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
159 return;
160 }
161}

99 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
100 CommandMsrwriteHelp();
101
102 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
103 return;
104 }
105 else
106 {
107 GetAddress = TRUE;
108 }
109 }
110 else
111 {
112 //
113 // Unkonwn parameter
114 //
115 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
116 CommandMsrwriteHelp();
117
118 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
119 return;
120 }
121 }
122
123 //
124 // Set the target msr (if not specific then it means all msrs)
125 //
126 Event->OptionalParam1 = SpecialTarget;
127
128 //
129 // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
130 //
131 if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
132 {
133 //
134 // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
135 // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
136 // already freed the Event and string buffers
137 //
138
139 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
140 return;
141 }
142
143 //
144 // Add the event to the kernel
145 //
146 if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
147 ActionBreakToDebugger,
148 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
149 ActionCustomCode,
150 ActionCustomCodeLength,
151 ActionScript,
152 ActionScriptLength))
153 {
154 //
155 // There was an error
156 //
157
158 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
159 return;
160 }
161}

53{
54 UINT32 StepCount;
55 DEBUGGER_REMOTE_STEPPING_REQUEST RequestFormat;
56
57 //
58 // Validate the commands
59 //
60 if (SplittedCommand.size() != 1 && SplittedCommand.size() != 2)
61 {
62 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the 'p'\n\n");
63 CommandPHelp();
64 return;
65 }
66
67 //
68 // Set type of request
69 //
70 RequestFormat = DEBUGGER_REMOTE_STEPPING_REQUEST_STEP_OVER;
71
72 //
73 // Check if the command has a counter parameter
74 //
75 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 2)
76 {
77 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(1), &StepCount))
78 {
79 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for [count]\n\n");
80 CommandPHelp();
81 return;
82 }
83 }
84 else
85 {
86 StepCount = 1;
87 }
88
89 //
90 // Check if the remote serial debuggee or user debugger are paused or not
91 //
92 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee || g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
93 {
94 //
95 // Check if the thread is paused or not
96 //
97 if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive && !g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsPaused)
98 {
99 ShowMessages("the target process is running, use the "
100 "'pause' command or press CTRL+C to pause the process\n");
101 return;
102 }
103
104 //
105 // Indicate that we're instrumenting
106 //
107 g_IsInstrumentingInstructions = TRUE;
108
109 for (size_t i = 0; i < StepCount; i++)
110 {
111 //
112 // For logging purpose
113 //
114 // ShowMessages("percentage : %f %% (%x)\n", 100.0 * (i /
115 // (float)StepCount), i);
116 //
117
118 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
119 {
120 //
121 // It's stepping over serial connection in kernel debugger
122 //
123 KdSendStepPacketToDebuggee(RequestFormat);
124 }
125 else
126 {
127 //
128 // It's stepping over user debugger
129 //
130 UdSendStepPacketToDebuggee(g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessDebuggingToken,
131 g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ThreadId,
132 RequestFormat);
133 }
134
135 if (!SplittedCommand.at(0).compare("pr"))
136 {
137 //
138 // Show registers
139 //
140 ShowAllRegisters();
141 if (i != StepCount - 1)
142 {
143 ShowMessages("\n");
144 }
145 }
146
147 //
148 // Check if user pressed CTRL+C
149 //
150 if (!g_IsInstrumentingInstructions)
151 {
152 break;
153 }
154 }
155
156 //
157 // We're not instrumenting instructions anymore
158 //
159 g_IsInstrumentingInstructions = FALSE;
160 }
161 else
162 {
163 ShowMessages("err, stepping (p) is not valid in the current context, you "
164 "should connect to a debuggee\n");
165 }
166}

139 // We use same buffer for input and output

143 AddressDetails.IsVirtual2Physical = FALSE;

168 Pid = GetCurrentProcessId();
169 AddressDetails.ProcessId = Pid;
170 }
171
172 //
173 // Send IOCTL
174 //
175 Status = DeviceIoControl(
176 g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
177 IOCTL_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // IO Control code
178 &AddressDetails, // Input Buffer to driver.
179 SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // Input buffer length

57{

103 //
104 // Query for nt!_EPROCESS.ImageFileName, nt!_EPROCESS.UniqueProcessId,
105 // nt!_EPROCESS.UniqueProcessId offset from the top of nt!_EPROCESS,
106 // and nt!PsActiveProcessHead address and check if we find them or not,
107 // otherwise, it means that the PDB for ntoskrnl.exe is not available
108 //
109 if (ScriptEngineGetFieldOffsetWrapper((CHAR *)"nt!_EPROCESS", (CHAR *)"ActiveProcessLinks", &OffsetOfActiveProcessLinks) &&
110 ScriptEngineGetFieldOffsetWrapper((CHAR *)"nt!_EPROCESS", (CHAR *)"ImageFileName", &OffsetOfImageFileName) &&
111 ScriptEngineGetFieldOffsetWrapper((CHAR *)"nt!_EPROCESS", (CHAR *)"UniqueProcessId", &OffsetOfUniqueProcessId) &&
112 SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress("nt!PsActiveProcessHead", &AddressOfActiveProcessHead))
113 {
114 //
115 // For test offsets and addresses
116 //
117
118 /*
119 ShowMessages("Address of ActiveProcessHead : %llx\n", AddressOfActiveProcessHead);
120 ShowMessages("Offset Of ActiveProcessLinks : 0x%x\n", OffsetOfActiveProcessLinks);
121 ShowMessages("Offset Of ImageFileName : 0x%x\n", OffsetOfImageFileName);
122 ShowMessages("Offset Of UniqueProcessId : 0x%x\n", OffsetOfUniqueProcessId);
123 */
124
125 ProcessListNeededItems.PsActiveProcessHead = AddressOfActiveProcessHead;
126 ProcessListNeededItems.ActiveProcessLinksOffset = OffsetOfActiveProcessLinks;
127 ProcessListNeededItems.ImageFileNameOffset = OffsetOfImageFileName;
128 ProcessListNeededItems.UniquePidOffset = OffsetOfUniqueProcessId;
129
130 if (!g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
131 {
132 //
133 // Get list of processes in VMI mode
134 //
135 ObjectShowProcessesOrThreadList(TRUE,

137 NULL,
138 NULL);
139 }

141 {
142 //
143 // Send the packet to show list of process
144 //
145 KdSendSwitchProcessPacketToDebuggee(DEBUGGEE_DETAILS_AND_SWITCH_PROCESS_GET_PROCESS_LIST,
146 NULL,
147 NULL,
148 FALSE,
149 &ProcessListNeededItems);
150 }
151 }
152 else
153 {
154 ShowMessages("err, the need offset to iterate over processes not found, "
155 "make sure to load ntoskrnl.exe's PDB file. use '.help .sym' for "
156 "more information\n");
157 return;
158 }
159 }
160 else
161 {
162 ShowMessages(
163 "err, unknown parameter at '%s'\n\n",
164 SplittedCommand.at(1).c_str());
165 CommandProcessHelp();
166 return;
167 }
168 }
169 else if (SplittedCommand.size() == 3)
170 {
171 //
172 // Check if it's connected to a remote debuggee or not
173 //
174 if (!g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
175 {
176 ShowMessages("err, you're not connected to any debuggee in Debugger Mode, "
177 "you can use the '.attach', or the '.detach' commands if you're "
178 "operating in VMI Mode\n");
179 return;
180 }
181
182 if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("pid"))
183 {
184 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(2), &TargetProcessId))
185 {
186 ShowMessages(
187 "please specify a correct hex value for the process id that you "
188 "want to operate on it\n\n");
189 CommandProcessHelp();
190 return;
191 }
192 }
193 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("process"))
194 {
195 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommand.at(2), &TargetProcess))
196 {
197 ShowMessages(
198 "please specify a correct hex value for the process (nt!_EPROCESS) that you "
199 "want to operate on it\n\n");
200 CommandProcessHelp();
201 return;
202 }
203 }
204 else
205 {
206 ShowMessages(
207 "err, unknown parameter at '%s'\n\n",
208 SplittedCommand.at(2).c_str());
209 CommandProcessHelp();
210 return;
211 }
212
213 //
214 // Check for switching method
215 //
216 if (!SplittedCommand.at(0).compare(".process2"))
217 {
218 IsSetByClkIntr = FALSE;
219 }
220 else
221 {
222 IsSetByClkIntr = TRUE;
223 }
224
225 //
226 // Send the packet to change process
227 //
228 KdSendSwitchProcessPacketToDebuggee(DEBUGGEE_DETAILS_AND_SWITCH_PROCESS_PERFORM_SWITCH,
229 TargetProcessId,
230 TargetProcess,
231 IsSetByClkIntr,
232 NULL);
233 }

92{
93 BOOL Status;
94 ULONG ReturnedLength;
95 UINT64 TargetVa;
96 UINT32 Pid = 0;
97 DEBUGGER_READ_PAGE_TABLE_ENTRIES_DETAILS AddressDetails = {0};
98 vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
99
100 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 1 || SplittedCommand.size() >= 5 ||
101 SplittedCommand.size() == 3)
102 {
103 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!pte'\n\n");
104 CommandPteHelp();
105 return;
106 }
107
108 //
109 // By default if the user-debugger is active, we use these commands
110 // on the memory layout of the debuggee process
111 //
112 if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
113 {
114 Pid = g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId;
115 }
116
117 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 2)
118 {
119 //
120 // It's just an address for current process
121 //
122 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1), &TargetVa))
123 {
124 //
125 // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
126 //
127 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
128 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1).c_str());
129 return;
130 }
131 }
132 else
133 {
134 //
135 // It might be address + pid
136 //
137 if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("pid"))
138 {
139 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(2), &Pid))
140 {
141 ShowMessages("incorrect address, please enter a valid process id\n");
142 return;
143 }
144
145 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(3), &TargetVa))
146 {
147 //
148 // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
149 //
150 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
151 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(3).c_str());
152 return;
153 }
154 }
155 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("pid"))
156 {
157 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1), &TargetVa))
158 {
159 //
160 // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
161 //
162 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
163 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1).c_str());
164 return;
165 }
166
167 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(3), &Pid))
168 {
169 ShowMessages("incorrect address, please enter a valid process id\n");
170 return;
171 }
172 }
173 else
174 {
175 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!pte'\n\n");
176 CommandPteHelp();
177 return;
178 }
179 }
180
181 //
182 // Prepare the buffer
183 // We use same buffer for input and output
184 //
185 AddressDetails.VirtualAddress = TargetVa;
186 AddressDetails.ProcessId = Pid; // null in debugger mode
187
188 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
189 {
190 //
191 // Check to prevent using process id in !pte command
192 //
193 if (Pid != 0)
194 {
195 ShowMessages(ASSERT_MESSAGE_CANNOT_SPECIFY_PID);
196 return;
197 }
198
199 //
200 // Send the request over serial kernel debugger
201 //
202
203 KdSendPtePacketToDebuggee(&AddressDetails);
204 }
205 else
206 {
207 AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
208
209 if (Pid == 0)
210 {
211 Pid = GetCurrentProcessId();
212 AddressDetails.ProcessId = Pid;
213 }
214
215 //
216 // Send IOCTL
217 //
218 Status = DeviceIoControl(
219 g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
220 IOCTL_DEBUGGER_READ_PAGE_TABLE_ENTRIES_DETAILS, // IO Control code
221 &AddressDetails, // Input Buffer to driver.
222 SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_READ_PAGE_TABLE_ENTRIES_DETAILS, // Input buffer length
223 &AddressDetails, // Output Buffer from driver.
224 SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_READ_PAGE_TABLE_ENTRIES_DETAILS, // Length of output
225 // buffer in bytes.
226 &ReturnedLength, // Bytes placed in buffer.
227 NULL // synchronous call
228 );
229
230 if (!Status)
231 {
232 ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code 0x%x\n", GetLastError());
233 return;
234 }
235
236 if (AddressDetails.KernelStatus != DEBUGGER_OPERATION_WAS_SUCCESSFUL)
237 {
238 ShowErrorMessage(AddressDetails.KernelStatus);
239 return;
240 }
241
242 //
243 // Show the results
244 //
245 CommandPteShowResults(TargetVa, &AddressDetails);
246 }
247}

VOID CommandRdmsr ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,

)

rdmsr command handler

Parameters

Command

VOID
40{
41 BOOL Status;
42 BOOL IsNextCoreId = FALSE;
43 BOOL SetMsr = FALSE;
44 DEBUGGER_READ_AND_WRITE_ON_MSR MsrReadRequest;
45 ULONG ReturnedLength;
46 UINT64 Msr;
47 UINT32 CoreNumer = DEBUGGER_READ_AND_WRITE_ON_MSR_APPLY_ALL_CORES;
48 SYSTEM_INFO SysInfo;
49 DWORD NumCPU;
50
51 if (SplittedCommand.size() >= 5)
52 {
53 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the 'rdmsr'\n\n");
54 CommandRdmsrHelp();
55 return;
56 }
57
58 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
59 {
60 if (!Section.compare(SplittedCommand.at(0)))
61 {
62 continue;
63 }
64
65 if (IsNextCoreId)
66 {
67 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &CoreNumer))
68 {
69 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for core id\n\n");
70 CommandRdmsrHelp();
71 return;
72 }
73 IsNextCoreId = FALSE;
74 continue;
75 }
76
77 if (!Section.compare("core"))
78 {
79 IsNextCoreId = TRUE;
80 continue;
81 }
82
83 if (SetMsr || !ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &Msr))
84 {
85 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to be read\n\n");
86 CommandRdmsrHelp();
87 return;
88 }
89 SetMsr = TRUE;
90 }
91
92 //
93 // Check if msr is set or not
94 //
95 if (!SetMsr)
96 {
97 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to be read\n\n");
98 CommandRdmsrHelp();
99 return;
100 }
101 if (IsNextCoreId)
102 {
103 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for core\n\n");
104 CommandRdmsrHelp();
105 return;
106 }
107
108 AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
109
110 MsrReadRequest.ActionType = DEBUGGER_MSR_READ;
111 MsrReadRequest.Msr = Msr;
112 MsrReadRequest.CoreNumber = CoreNumer;
113
114 //
115 // Find logical cores count
116 //
117 GetSystemInfo(&SysInfo);
118 NumCPU = SysInfo.dwNumberOfProcessors;
119
120 //
121 // allocate buffer for transfering messages
122 //
123 UINT64 * OutputBuffer = (UINT64 *)malloc(sizeof(UINT64) * NumCPU);
124
125 ZeroMemory(OutputBuffer, sizeof(UINT64) * NumCPU);
126
127 Status = DeviceIoControl(
128 g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
129 IOCTL_DEBUGGER_READ_OR_WRITE_MSR, // IO Control code
130 &MsrReadRequest, // Input Buffer to driver.
131 SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_READ_AND_WRITE_ON_MSR, // Input buffer length
132 OutputBuffer, // Output Buffer from driver.
133 sizeof(UINT64) * NumCPU, // Length of output buffer in bytes.
134 &ReturnedLength, // Bytes placed in buffer.
135 NULL // synchronous call
136 );
137
138 if (!Status)
139 {
140 ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code (%x), either msr index or core id is invalid\n",
141 GetLastError());
142 free(OutputBuffer);
143 return;
144 }
145
146 //
147 // btw, %x is enough, no need to %llx
148 //
149 if (CoreNumer == DEBUGGER_READ_AND_WRITE_ON_MSR_APPLY_ALL_CORES)
150 {
151 //
152 // Show all cores
153 //
154 for (size_t i = 0; i < NumCPU; i++)
155 {
156 ShowMessages("core : 0x%x - msr[%llx] = %s\n", i, Msr, SeparateTo64BitValue((OutputBuffer[i])).c_str());
157 }
158 }
159 else
160 {
161 //
162 // Show for a single-core
163 //
164 ShowMessages("core : 0x%x - msr[%llx] = %s\n", CoreNumer, Msr, SeparateTo64BitValue((OutputBuffer[0])).c_str());
165 }
166
167 //
168 // Free the buffer
169 //
170 free(OutputBuffer);
171}

73{

79 BOOLEAN IsNextLength = FALSE;

81 UINT32 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive = 0;
82
83 string FirstCommand = SplittedCommand.front();
84
85 //
86 // By default if the user-debugger is active, we use these commands
87 // on the memory layout of the debuggee process
88 //
89 if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
90 {
91 Pid = g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId;
92 }
93
94 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 1)
95 {
96 //
97 // Means that user entered one command without any parameter
98 //
99 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '%s' command\n\n", FirstCommand.c_str());
100 CommandReadMemoryAndDisassemblerHelp();
101 return;
102 }
103
104 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
105 {
106 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive++;
107
108 if (IsFirstCommand)
109 {
110 IsFirstCommand = FALSE;
111 continue;
112 }
113 if (IsNextProcessId == TRUE)
114 {
115 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &Pid))
116 {
117 ShowMessages("err, you should enter a valid process id\n\n");
118 return;
119 }
120 IsNextProcessId = FALSE;
121 continue;
122 }
123
124 if (IsNextLength == TRUE)
125 {
126 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &Length))
127 {
128 ShowMessages("err, you should enter a valid length\n\n");
129 return;
130 }
131 IsNextLength = FALSE;
132 continue;
133 }
134
135 if (!Section.compare("l"))
136 {
137 IsNextLength = TRUE;
138 continue;
139 }
140
141 if (!Section.compare("pid"))
142 {
143 IsNextProcessId = TRUE;
144 continue;
145 }
146
147 //
148 // Probably it's address
149 //
150 if (TargetAddress == 0)
151 {
152 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1),
153 &TargetAddress))
154 {
155 //
156 // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
157 //
158 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
159 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
160 return;
161 }
162 }
163 else
164 {
165 //
166 // User inserts two address
167 //
168 ShowMessages("err, incorrect use of the '%s' command\n\n",
169 FirstCommand.c_str());
170 CommandReadMemoryAndDisassemblerHelp();
171
172 return;
173 }
174 }
175
176 if (!TargetAddress)
177 {
178 //
179 // User inserts two address
180 //
181 ShowMessages("err, please enter a valid address\n\n");
182
183 return;
184 }
185
186 if (Length == 0)
187 {
188 //
189 // Default length (user doesn't specified)
190 //
191 if (!FirstCommand.compare("u") ||
192 !FirstCommand.compare("!u") ||
193 !FirstCommand.compare("u64") ||
194 !FirstCommand.compare("!u64"))
195 {
196 Length = 0x40;
197 }
198 else
199 {
200 Length = 0x80;
201 }
202 }
203
204 if (IsNextLength || IsNextProcessId)
205 {
206 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '%s' command\n\n", FirstCommand.c_str());
207 CommandReadMemoryAndDisassemblerHelp();
208 return;
209 }
210
211 //
212 // Check to prevent using process id in d* and u* commands
213 //
214 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee && Pid != 0)
215 {
216 ShowMessages(ASSERT_MESSAGE_CANNOT_SPECIFY_PID);
217 return;
218 }
219
220 if (Pid == 0)
221 {
222 //
223 // Default process we read from current process
224 //
225 Pid = GetCurrentProcessId();
226 }
227
228 if (!FirstCommand.compare("db"))
229 {
230 HyperDbgReadMemoryAndDisassemble(DEBUGGER_SHOW_COMMAND_DB,
231 TargetAddress,
232 DEBUGGER_READ_VIRTUAL_ADDRESS,
233 READ_FROM_KERNEL,
234 Pid,
235 Length,
236 NULL);

241 TargetAddress,
242 DEBUGGER_READ_VIRTUAL_ADDRESS,
243 READ_FROM_KERNEL,
244 Pid,
245 Length,
246 NULL);
247 }
248 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("dd"))
249 {
250 HyperDbgReadMemoryAndDisassemble(DEBUGGER_SHOW_COMMAND_DD,
251 TargetAddress,
252 DEBUGGER_READ_VIRTUAL_ADDRESS,
253 READ_FROM_KERNEL,
254 Pid,
255 Length,
256 NULL);
257 }
258 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("dq"))
259 {
260 HyperDbgReadMemoryAndDisassemble(DEBUGGER_SHOW_COMMAND_DQ,
261 TargetAddress,
262 DEBUGGER_READ_VIRTUAL_ADDRESS,
263 READ_FROM_KERNEL,
264 Pid,
265 Length,
266 NULL);
267 }
268 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("!db"))
269 {
270 HyperDbgReadMemoryAndDisassemble(DEBUGGER_SHOW_COMMAND_DB,
271 TargetAddress,
272 DEBUGGER_READ_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS,
273 READ_FROM_KERNEL,
274 Pid,
275 Length,
276 NULL);
277 }
278 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("!dc"))
279 {
280 HyperDbgReadMemoryAndDisassemble(DEBUGGER_SHOW_COMMAND_DC,
281 TargetAddress,
282 DEBUGGER_READ_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS,
283 READ_FROM_KERNEL,
284 Pid,
285 Length,
286 NULL);
287 }
288 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("!dd"))
289 {
290 HyperDbgReadMemoryAndDisassemble(DEBUGGER_SHOW_COMMAND_DD,
291 TargetAddress,
292 DEBUGGER_READ_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS,
293 READ_FROM_KERNEL,
294 Pid,
295 Length,
296 NULL);
297 }
298 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("!dq"))
299 {
300 HyperDbgReadMemoryAndDisassemble(DEBUGGER_SHOW_COMMAND_DQ,
301 TargetAddress,
302 DEBUGGER_READ_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS,
303 READ_FROM_KERNEL,
304 Pid,
305 Length,
306 NULL);
307 }
308
309 //
310 // Disassembler (!u or u or u2 !u2)
311 //
312 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("u") || !FirstCommand.compare("u64"))
313 {

317 DEBUGGER_READ_VIRTUAL_ADDRESS,
318 READ_FROM_KERNEL,
319 Pid,
320 Length,
321 NULL);
322 }
323 else if (!FirstCommand.compare("!u") || !FirstCommand.compare("!u64"))
324 {

328 DEBUGGER_READ_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS,

330 Pid,
331 Length,
332 NULL);
333 }

339 DEBUGGER_READ_VIRTUAL_ADDRESS,

341 Pid,
342 Length,
343 NULL);
344 }

◆ CommandSearchMemory()

VOID CommandSearchMemory ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,
string  Command 
)

!s* s* commands handler

Parameters
SplittedCommand
Command
Returns
VOID
139{
140 BOOL SetAddress = FALSE;
141 BOOL SetValue = FALSE;
142 BOOL SetProcId = FALSE;
143 BOOL NextIsProcId = FALSE;
144 BOOL SetLength = FALSE;
145 BOOL NextIsLength = FALSE;
146 DEBUGGER_SEARCH_MEMORY SearchMemoryRequest = {0};
147 UINT64 Address;
148 UINT64 Value = 0;
149 UINT64 Length = 0;
150 UINT32 ProcId = 0;
151 UINT32 CountOfValues = 0;
152 UINT32 FinalSize = 0;
153 UINT64 * FinalBuffer = NULL;
154 vector<UINT64> ValuesToEdit;
155 vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
156 UINT32 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive = 0;
157
158 //
159 // By default if the user-debugger is active, we use these commands
160 // on the memory layout of the debuggee process
161 //
162 if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
163 {
164 ProcId = g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId;
165 }
166
167 if (SplittedCommand.size() <= 4)
168 {
169 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the 's*'\n\n");
170 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
171 return;
172 }
173
174 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
175 {
176 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive++;
177
178 if (!Section.compare(SplittedCommand.at(0)))
179 {
180 if (!Section.compare("!sb"))
181 {
182 SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
183 SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_BYTE;
184 }
185 else if (!Section.compare("!sd"))
186 {
187 SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
188 SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_DWORD;
189 }
190 else if (!Section.compare("!sq"))
191 {
192 SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
193 SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_QWORD;
194 }
195 else if (!Section.compare("sb"))
196 {
197 SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
198 SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_BYTE;
199 }
200 else if (!Section.compare("sd"))
201 {
202 SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
203 SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_DWORD;
204 }
205 else if (!Section.compare("sq"))
206 {
207 SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
208 SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_QWORD;
209 }
210 else
211 {
212 //
213 // What's this? :(
214 //
215 ShowMessages("unknown error happened !\n\n");
216 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
217 return;
218 }
219
220 continue;
221 }
222
223 if (NextIsProcId)
224 {
225 //
226 // It's a process id
227 //
228 NextIsProcId = FALSE;
229
230 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &ProcId))
231 {
232 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex prcoess id\n\n");
233 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
234 return;
235 }
236 else
237 {
238 //
239 // Means that the proc id is set, next we should read value
240 //
241 continue;
242 }
243 }
244
245 if (NextIsLength)
246 {
247 //
248 // It's a length
249 //
250 NextIsLength = FALSE;
251
252 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &Length))
253 {
254 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex length\n\n");
255 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
256 return;
257 }
258 else
259 {
260 //
261 // Means that the proc id is set, next we should read value
262 //
263 SetLength = TRUE;
264 continue;
265 }
266 }
267
268 //
269 // Check if it's a process id or not
270 //
271 if (!SetProcId && !Section.compare("pid"))
272 {
273 NextIsProcId = TRUE;
274 continue;
275 }
276
277 //
278 // Check if it's a length or not
279 //
280 if (!SetLength && !Section.compare("l"))
281 {
282 NextIsLength = TRUE;
283 continue;
284 }
285
286 if (!SetAddress)
287 {
288 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1), &Address))
289 {
290 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
291 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
292 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
293 return;
294 }
295 else
296 {
297 //
298 // Means that the address is set, next we should read value
299 //
300 SetAddress = TRUE;
301 continue;
302 }
303 }
304
305 if (SetAddress)
306 {
307 //
308 // Remove the hex notations
309 //
310 if (Section.rfind("0x", 0) == 0 || Section.rfind("0X", 0) == 0 ||
311 Section.rfind("\\x", 0) == 0 || Section.rfind("\\X", 0) == 0)
312 {
313 Section = Section.erase(0, 2);
314 }
315 else if (Section.rfind('x', 0) == 0 || Section.rfind('X', 0) == 0)
316 {
317 Section = Section.erase(0, 1);
318 }
319 Section.erase(remove(Section.begin(), Section.end(), '`'), Section.end());
320
321 //
322 // Check if the value is valid based on byte counts
323 //
324 if (SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize == SEARCH_BYTE && Section.size() >= 3)
325 {
326 ShowMessages("please specify a byte (hex) value for 'sb' or '!sb'\n\n");
327 return;
328 }
329 if (SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize == SEARCH_DWORD && Section.size() >= 9)
330 {
331 ShowMessages(
332 "please specify a dword (hex) value for 'sd' or '!sd'\n\n");
333 return;
334 }
335 if (SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize == SEARCH_QWORD &&
336 Section.size() >= 17)
337 {
338 ShowMessages(
339 "please specify a qword (hex) value for 'sq' or '!sq'\n\n");
340 return;
341 }
342
343 //
344 // Qword is checked by the following function, no need to double
345 // check it above.
346 //
347 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &Value))
348 {
349 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to search in the "
350 "memory content\n\n");
351 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
352 return;
353 }
354 else
355 {
356 //
357 // Add it to the list
358 //
359 ValuesToEdit.push_back(Value);
360
361 //
362 // Keep track of values to modify
363 //
364 CountOfValues++;
365
366 if (!SetValue)
367 {
368 //
369 // At least on walue is there
370 //
371 SetValue = TRUE;
372 }
373 continue;
374 }
375 }
376 }
377
378 //
379 // Check to prevent using process id in s* commands
380 //
381 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee && ProcId != 0)
382 {
383 ShowMessages(ASSERT_MESSAGE_CANNOT_SPECIFY_PID);
384 return;
385 }
386
387 if (ProcId == 0)
388 {
389 ProcId = GetCurrentProcessId();
390 }
391
392 //
393 // Fill the structure
394 //
395 SearchMemoryRequest.ProcessId = ProcId;
396 SearchMemoryRequest.Address = Address;
397 SearchMemoryRequest.CountOf64Chunks = CountOfValues;
398
399 //
400 // Check if address and value are set or not
401 //
402 if (!SetAddress)
403 {
404 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex address\n\n");
405 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
406 return;
407 }
408 if (!SetValue)
409 {
410 ShowMessages(
411 "please specify a correct hex value as the content to search\n\n");
412 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
413 return;
414 }
415 if (!SetLength)
416 {
417 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value as the length\n\n");
418 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
419 return;
420 }
421 if (NextIsProcId)
422 {
423 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value as the process id\n\n");
424 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
425 return;
426 }
427 if (NextIsLength)
428 {
429 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex length\n\n");
430 CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
431 return;
432 }
433
434 //
435 // Now it's time to put everything together in one structure
436 //
437 FinalSize = (CountOfValues * sizeof(UINT64)) + SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_SEARCH_MEMORY;
438
439 //
440 // Set the size
441 //
442 SearchMemoryRequest.FinalStructureSize = FinalSize;
443
444 //
445 // Set the length
446 //
447 SearchMemoryRequest.Length = Length;
448
449 if (!g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
450 {
451 AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
452 }
453
454 //
455 // Allocate structure + buffer
456 //
457 FinalBuffer = (UINT64 *)malloc(FinalSize);
458
459 if (!FinalBuffer)
460 {
461 ShowMessages("unable to allocate memory\n\n");
462 return;
463 }
464
465 //
466 // Zero the buffer
467 //
468 ZeroMemory(FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
469
470 //
471 // Copy the structure on top of the allocated buffer
472 //
473 memcpy(FinalBuffer, &SearchMemoryRequest, SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_SEARCH_MEMORY);
474
475 //
476 // Put the values in 64 bit structures
477 //
478 std::copy(ValuesToEdit.begin(), ValuesToEdit.end(), (UINT64 *)((UINT64)FinalBuffer + SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_SEARCH_MEMORY));
479
480 //
481 // Check if it's a connection in debugger mode
482 //
483 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
484 {
485 //
486 // The buffer should be sent to the debugger
487 //
488 KdSendSearchRequestPacketToDebuggee(FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
489 }
490 else
491 {
492 //
493 // it's a local connection, send the buffer directly
494 //
495 CommandSearchSendRequest(FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
496 }
497
498 //
499 // Free the buffers
500 //
501 free(FinalBuffer);
502}

171 //
172 if (CommandSettingsGetValueFromConfigFile("AsmSyntax", OptionValue))
173 {
174 //
175 // The user tries to set a value as the syntax
176 //
177 if (!OptionValue.compare("intel"))
178 {
179 g_DisassemblerSyntax = 1;
180 }
181 else if (!OptionValue.compare("att") ||
182 !OptionValue.compare("at&t"))
183 {
184 g_DisassemblerSyntax = 2;
185 }
186 else if (!OptionValue.compare("masm"))
187 {
188 g_DisassemblerSyntax = 3;
189 }
190 else
191 {
192 //
193 // Sth is incorrect
194 //
195 ShowMessages("err, incorrect assembly syntax settings\n");
196 }
197 }
198
199 //
200 // Set the auto unpause
201 //
202 if (CommandSettingsGetValueFromConfigFile("AutoUnpause", OptionValue))
203 {
204 if (!OptionValue.compare("on"))
205 {
206 g_AutoUnpause = TRUE;
207 }
208 else if (!OptionValue.compare("off"))
209 {
210 g_AutoUnpause = FALSE;
211 }
212 else
213 {
214 //
215 // Sth is incorrect
216 //
217 ShowMessages("err, incorrect auto unpause settings\n");
218 }
219 }
220
221 //
222 // Set the auto flush
223 //
224 if (CommandSettingsGetValueFromConfigFile("AutoFlush", OptionValue))
225 {
226 if (!OptionValue.compare("on"))
227 {
228 g_AutoFlush = TRUE;
229 }
230 else if (!OptionValue.compare("off"))
231 {
232 g_AutoFlush = FALSE;
233 }
234 else
235 {
236 //
237 // Sth is incorrect
238 //
239 ShowMessages("err, incorrect auto flush settings\n");
240 }
241 }
242
243 //
244 // Set the address conversion
245 //
246 if (CommandSettingsGetValueFromConfigFile("AddrConv", OptionValue))
247 {
248 if (!OptionValue.compare("on"))
249 {
250 g_AddressConversion = TRUE;
251 }
252 else if (!OptionValue.compare("off"))
253 {
254 g_AddressConversion = FALSE;
255 }
256 else
257 {

259 // Sth is incorrect
260 //
261 ShowMessages("err, incorrect address conversion settings\n");
262 }
263 }

130

147 //

153 }
