55{
56 UINT64 BaseAddress = NULL;
57 UINT32 UserProcessId = NULL;
58
59 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 1)
60 {
61 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.sym'\n\n");
62 CommandSymHelp();
63 return;
64 }
65
66 if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("table"))
67 {
68 //
69 // Validate params
70 //
71 if (SplittedCommand.size() != 2)
72 {
73 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.sym'\n\n");
74 CommandSymHelp();
75 return;
76 }
77
78 //
79 // Show symbol table
80 //
81 SymbolBuildAndShowSymbolTable();
82 }
83 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("load") || !SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("download"))
84 {
85 //
86 // Validate params
87 //
88 if (SplittedCommand.size() != 2)
89 {
90 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.sym'\n\n");
91 CommandSymHelp();
92 return;
93 }
94
95 //
96 // Load and download available symbols
97 //
98 if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("load"))
99 {
100 SymbolLoadOrDownloadSymbols(FALSE, FALSE);
101 }
102 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("download"))
103 {
104 SymbolLoadOrDownloadSymbols(TRUE, FALSE);
105 }
106 }
107 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("reload"))
108 {
109 //
110 // Validate params
111 //
112 if (SplittedCommand.size() != 2 && SplittedCommand.size() != 4)
113 {
114 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.sym'\n\n");
115 CommandSymHelp();
116 return;
117 }
118
119 //
120 // Check for process id
121 //
122 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 4)
123 {
124 if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("pid"))
125 {
126 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(3), &UserProcessId))
127 {
128 //
129 // couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
130 //
131 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
132 SplittedCommand.at(3).c_str());
133 CommandSymHelp();
134 return;
135 }
136 }
137 else
138 {
139 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.sym'\n\n");
140 CommandSymHelp();
141 return;
142 }
143 }
144
145 //
146 // Refresh and reload symbols
147 //
148 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
149 {
150 //
151 // Update symbol table from remote debuggee in debugger-mode
152 //
153 SymbolReloadSymbolTableInDebuggerMode(UserProcessId);
154 }
155 else
156 {
157 //
158 // Check if user explicitly specified the process id
159 //
160 if (UserProcessId == NULL)
161 {
162 //
163 // User didn't explicitly specified the process id, so
164 // if it's a user-debugger process, we use the modules
165 // of the target user-debuggee's process, otherwise,
166 // the current process (HyperDbg's process) is specified
167 //
168 if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
169 {
170 UserProcessId = g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId;
171 }
172 else
173 {
174 UserProcessId = GetCurrentProcessId();
175 }
176 }
177
178 //
179 // Build locally and reload it
180 //
181 if (SymbolLocalReload(UserProcessId))
182 {
183 ShowMessages("symbol table updated successfully\n");
184 }
185 }
186 }
187 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("unload"))
188 {
189 //
190 // Validate params
191 //
192 if (SplittedCommand.size() != 2)
193 {
194 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.sym'\n\n");
195 CommandSymHelp();
196 return;
197 }
198
199 //
200 // unload without any parameters, means that unload
201 // all the symbols
202 //
203 ScriptEngineUnloadAllSymbolsWrapper();
204
205 //
206 // Size is 3 there is module name (not working ! I don't know why)
207 //
208 // ScriptEngineUnloadModuleSymbolWrapper((char *)SplittedCommand.at(2).c_str());
209 }
210 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("add"))
211 {
212 //
213 // Validate params
214 //
215 if (SplittedCommand.size() < 6)
216 {
217 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.sym'\n\n");
218 CommandSymHelp();
219 return;
220 }
221
222 if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("base"))
223 {
224 string Delimiter = "";
225 string PathToPdb = "";
226 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(SplittedCommand.at(3), &BaseAddress))
227 {
228 ShowMessages("please add a valid hex address to be used as the base address\n\n");
229 CommandSymHelp();
230 return;
231 }
232
233 //
234 // Base address is now valid, check if next parameter is path
235 //
236 if (SplittedCommand.at(4).compare("path"))
237 {
238 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.sym'\n\n");
239 CommandSymHelp();
240 return;
241 }
242
243 //
244 // The rest of command is pdb path
245 //
246 Delimiter = "path ";
247 PathToPdb = Command.substr(Command.find(Delimiter) + 5, Command.size());
248
249 //
250 // Check if pdb file exists or not
251 //
252 if (!IsFileExistA(PathToPdb.c_str()))
253 {
254 ShowMessages("pdb file not found\n");
255 return;
256 }
257
258 ShowMessages("loading module symbol at '%s'\n", PathToPdb.c_str());
259
260 //
261 // Load the pdb file (the validation of pdb file is checked into pdb
262 // parsing functions)
263 //
264 ScriptEngineLoadFileSymbolWrapper(BaseAddress, PathToPdb.c_str(), NULL);
265 }
266 else
267 {
268 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '.sym'\n\n");
269 CommandSymHelp();
270 return;
271 }
272 }
273 else
274 {
275 ShowMessages("unknown parameter at '%s'\n\n", SplittedCommand.at(1).c_str());
276 CommandSymHelp();
277 return;
278 }
279}

118 else
119 {
120 if (!InterpretGeneralEventAndActionsFields(
121 &SplittedCommand,
122 &SplittedCommandCaseSensitive,
123 SYSCALL_HOOK_EFER_SYSRET,
124 &Event,
125 &EventLength,
126 &ActionBreakToDebugger,
127 &ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
128 &ActionCustomCode,
129 &ActionCustomCodeLength,
130 &ActionScript,
131 &ActionScriptLength,
132 &EventParsingErrorCause))
133 {
134 return;
135 }
136 }
137
138 //
139 // Interpret command specific details (if any)
140 //
141
142 //
143 // Currently we do not support any extra argument for !sysret command
144 // it is because we don't know how to find syscall number in sysret
145 // and we don't wanna deal with dynamic mapping of rcx (user stack)
146 // in vmx-root
147 //
148 if (!Cmd.compare("!syscall") || !Cmd.compare("!syscall2"))
149 {
150 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
151 {
152 if (!Section.compare("!syscall") ||
153 !Section.compare("!syscall2") ||
154 !Section.compare("!sysret") ||
155 !Section.compare("!sysret2"))
156 {
157 continue;
158 }
159
160 else if (!GetSyscallNumber)
161 {
162 //
163 // It's probably a syscall address
164 //
165 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &SpecialTarget))
166 {
167 //
168 // Unkonwn parameter
169 //
170 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
171
172 if (!Cmd.compare("!syscall") || !Cmd.compare("!syscall2"))
173 {
174 CommandSyscallHelp();
175 }
176 else
177 {
178 CommandSysretHelp();
179 }
180
181 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
182 return;
183 }
184 else
185 {
186 GetSyscallNumber = TRUE;
187 }
188 }
189 else
190 {
191 //
192 // Unkonwn parameter
193 //
194 ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
195
196 if (!Cmd.compare("!syscall") || !Cmd.compare("!syscall2"))
197 {
198 CommandSyscallHelp();
199 }
200 else
201 {
202 CommandSysretHelp();
203 }
204
205 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
206 return;
207 }
208 }
209
210 //
211 // Set the target syscall
212 //
213 Event->OptionalParam1 = SpecialTarget;
214 }
215
216 //
217 // Set whether it's !syscall or !syscall2 or !sysret or !sysret2
218 //
219 if (!Cmd.compare("!syscall2") || !Cmd.compare("!sysret2"))
220 {
221 //
222 // It's a !syscall2 or !sysret2
223 //
224 Event->OptionalParam2 = DEBUGGER_EVENT_SYSCALL_SYSRET_HANDLE_ALL_UD;
225 }
226 else
227 {
228 //
229 // It's a !syscall or !sysret
230 //
231 Event->OptionalParam2 = DEBUGGER_EVENT_SYSCALL_SYSRET_SAFE_ACCESS_MEMORY;
232 }
233
234 //
235 // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
236 //
237 if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
238 {
239 //
240 // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
241 // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
242 // already freed the Event and string buffers
243 //
244
245 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
246 return;
247 }
248
249 //
250 // Add the event to the kernel
251 //
252 if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
253 ActionBreakToDebugger,
254 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
255 ActionCustomCode,
256 ActionCustomCodeLength,
257 ActionScript,
258 ActionScriptLength))
259 {
260 //
261 // There was an error
262 //
263
264 FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
265 return;
266 }
267}
DEBUGGER_EVENT_SYSCALL_ALL_SYSRET_OR_SYSCALLS

Apply to all syscalls and sysrets.

139 //

149 //

153 }
154 }
155
156 //
157 // We're not instrumenting instructions anymore
158 //
159 g_IsInstrumentingInstructions = FALSE;
160 }
161 else

164 "should connect to a debuggee\n");
165 }
166}

50{
51 BOOL Status;
52 ULONG ReturnedLength;
53 UINT64 TargetVa;
54 UINT32 Pid = 0;
55 DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS AddressDetails = {0};
56 vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
57
58 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 1 || SplittedCommand.size() >= 5 ||
59 SplittedCommand.size() == 3)
60 {
61 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!va2pa'\n\n");
62 CommandVa2paHelp();
63 return;
64 }
65
66 //
67 // By default if the user-debugger is active, we use these commands
68 // on the memory layout of the debuggee process
69 //
70 if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
71 {
72 Pid = g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId;
73 }
74
75 if (SplittedCommand.size() == 2)
76 {
77 //
78 // It's just an address for current process
79 //
80 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1), &TargetVa))
81 {
82 //
83 // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
84 //
85 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
86 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1).c_str());
87 return;
88 }
89 }
90 else
91 {
92 //
93 // It might be address + pid
94 //
95 if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("pid"))
96 {
97 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(2), &Pid))
98 {
99 ShowMessages("incorrect address, please enter a valid process id\n");
100 return;
101 }
102
103 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(3), &TargetVa))
104 {
105 //
106 // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
107 //
108 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
109 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(3).c_str());
110 return;
111 }
112 }
113 else if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("pid"))
114 {
115 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1), &TargetVa))
116 {
117 //
118 // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
119 //
120 ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
121 SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1).c_str());
122 return;
123 }
124
125 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(3), &Pid))
126 {
127 ShowMessages("incorrect address, please enter a valid process id\n");
128 return;
129 }
130 }
131 else
132 {
133 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the '!va2pa'\n\n");
134 CommandVa2paHelp();
135 return;
136 }
137 }
138
139 //
140 // Prepare the buffer
141 // We use same buffer for input and output
142 //
143 AddressDetails.VirtualAddress = TargetVa;
144 AddressDetails.ProcessId = Pid; // null in debugger mode
145 AddressDetails.IsVirtual2Physical = TRUE;
146
147 if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
148 {
149 //
150 // Check to prevent using process id in !va2pa command
151 //
152 if (Pid != 0)
153 {
154 ShowMessages(ASSERT_MESSAGE_CANNOT_SPECIFY_PID);
155 return;
156 }
157
158 //
159 // Send the request over serial kernel debugger
160 //
161
162 KdSendVa2paAndPa2vaPacketToDebuggee(&AddressDetails);
163 }
164 else
165 {
166 AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
167
168 if (Pid == 0)
169 {
170 Pid = GetCurrentProcessId();
171 AddressDetails.ProcessId = Pid;
172 }
173
174 //
175 // Send IOCTL
176 //
177 Status = DeviceIoControl(
178 g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
179 IOCTL_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // IO Control code
180 &AddressDetails, // Input Buffer to driver.
181 SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // Input buffer length
182 &AddressDetails, // Output Buffer from driver.
183 SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // Length of output
184 // buffer in bytes.
185 &ReturnedLength, // Bytes placed in buffer.
186 NULL // synchronous call
187 );
188
189 if (!Status)
190 {
191 ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code 0x%x\n", GetLastError());
192 return;
193 }
194
195 if (AddressDetails.KernelStatus == DEBUGGER_OPERATION_WAS_SUCCESSFUL)
196 {
197 //
198 // Show the results
199 //
200 ShowMessages("%llx\n", AddressDetails.PhysicalAddress);
201 }
202 else
203 {
204 //
205 // An err occurred, no results
206 //
207 ShowErrorMessage(AddressDetails.KernelStatus);
208 }
209 }
210}

42{
43 BOOL Status;

52 if (SplittedCommand.size() >= 6)
53 {
54 ShowMessages("incorrect use of the 'wrmsr'\n\n");
55 CommandWrmsrHelp();
56 return;
57 }
58
59 for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
60 {
61 if (!Section.compare(SplittedCommand.at(0)))
62 {
63 continue;
64 }
65
66 if (IsNextCoreId)
67 {
68 if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &CoreNumer))
69 {
70 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for core id\n\n");
71 CommandWrmsrHelp();
72 return;
73 }
74 IsNextCoreId = FALSE;
75 continue;
76 }
77
78 if (!Section.compare("core"))
79 {
80 IsNextCoreId = TRUE;
81 continue;
82 }
83
84 if (!SetMsr)
85 {
86 if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &Msr))
87 {
88 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to be read\n\n");
89 CommandWrmsrHelp();
90 return;
91 }
92 else
93 {
94 //
95 // Means that the MSR is set, next we should read value
96 //
97 SetMsr = TRUE;
98 continue;
99 }
100 }
101
102 if (SetMsr)
103 {
104 if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(Section, &Value))
105 {
106 ShowMessages(
107 "please specify a correct hex value or an expression to put on the msr\n\n");
108 CommandWrmsrHelp();
109 return;
110 }
111 else
112 {
113 SetValue = TRUE;
114 continue;
115 }
116 }
117 }
118
119 //
120 // Check if msr is set or not
121 //
122 if (!SetMsr)
123 {
124 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to write\n\n");
125 CommandWrmsrHelp();
126 return;
127 }
128 if (!SetValue)
129 {
130 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to put on msr\n\n");
131 CommandWrmsrHelp();
132 return;
133 }
134 if (IsNextCoreId)
135 {
136 ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for core\n\n");
137 CommandWrmsrHelp();
138 return;
139 }
140
141 AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
142
143 MsrWriteRequest.ActionType = DEBUGGER_MSR_WRITE;
144 MsrWriteRequest.Msr = Msr;
145 MsrWriteRequest.CoreNumber = CoreNumer;
146 MsrWriteRequest.Value = Value;
147
148 Status = DeviceIoControl(
149 g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
150 IOCTL_DEBUGGER_READ_OR_WRITE_MSR, // IO Control code
151 &MsrWriteRequest, // Input Buffer to driver.
152 SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_READ_AND_WRITE_ON_MSR, // Input buffer length
153 NULL, // Output Buffer from driver.
154 NULL, // Length of output buffer in bytes.
155 NULL, // Bytes placed in buffer.
156 NULL // synchronous call
157 );
158
159 if (!Status)
160 {
161 ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code (%x), either msr index or core id is invalid\n",
162 GetLastError());
163 return;
164 }
165
166 ShowMessages("\n");
167}

418 ZydisDecodedOperand operands[ZYDIS_MAX_OPERAND_COUNT];
419 UINT64 CurrentRip = 0;
420 int instr_decoded = 0;
421 ZydisDecodedInstruction instruction;
422 char buffer[256];
423 UINT32 MaximumInstrDecoded = 1;
424
425 if (ZydisGetVersion() != ZYDIS_VERSION)
426 {
427 ShowMessages("invalid Zydis version\n");
428 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_ERROR;
429 }
430
431 if (Isx86_64)
432 {
433 ZydisDecoderInit(&decoder, ZYDIS_MACHINE_MODE_LONG_64, ZYDIS_STACK_WIDTH_64);
434 }
435 else
436 {
437 ZydisDecoderInit(&decoder, ZYDIS_MACHINE_MODE_LONG_COMPAT_32, ZYDIS_STACK_WIDTH_32);
438 }
439
440 ZydisFormatterInit(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_STYLE_INTEL);
441
442 ZydisFormatterSetProperty(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_PROP_FORCE_SEGMENT, ZYAN_TRUE);
443 ZydisFormatterSetProperty(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_PROP_FORCE_SIZE, ZYAN_TRUE);
444
445 //
446 // Replace the `ZYDIS_FORMATTER_FUNC_PRINT_ADDRESS_ABS` function that
447 // formats the absolute addresses
448 //
449 default_print_address_absolute = (ZydisFormatterFunc)&ZydisFormatterPrintAddressAbsolute;
450 ZydisFormatterSetHook(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_FUNC_PRINT_ADDRESS_ABS, (const void **)&default_print_address_absolute);
451
452 while (ZYAN_SUCCESS(ZydisDecoderDecodeFull(&decoder, BufferToDisassemble, BuffLength, &instruction, operands)))
453 {
454 //
455 // We have to pass a `runtime_address` different to
456 // `ZYDIS_RUNTIME_ADDRESS_NONE` to enable printing of absolute addresses
457 //
458
459 // ZydisFormatterFormatInstruction(&formatter, &instruction, operands, instruction.operand_count_visible, &buffer[0], sizeof(buffer), (ZyanU64)CurrentRip, ZYAN_NULL);
460
461 switch (instruction.mnemonic)
462 {
463 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JO:
464
465 //
466 // Jump if overflow (jo)
467 //
468 if (Rflags.OverflowFlag)
469 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
470 else
471 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
472
473 break;
474
475 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNO:
476
477 //
478 // Jump if not overflow (jno)
479 //
480 if (!Rflags.OverflowFlag)
481 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
482 else
483 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
484
485 break;
486
487 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JS:
488
489 //
490 // Jump if sign
491 //
492 if (Rflags.SignFlag)
493 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
494 else
495 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
496
497 break;
498
499 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNS:
500
501 //
502 // Jump if not sign
503 //
504 if (!Rflags.SignFlag)
505 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
506 else
507 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
508
509 break;
510
511 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JZ:
512
513 //
514 // Jump if equal (je),
515 // Jump if zero (jz)
516 //
517 if (Rflags.ZeroFlag)
518 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
519 else
520 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
521
522 break;
523
524 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNZ:
525
526 //
527 // Jump if not equal (jne),
528 // Jump if not zero (jnz)
529 //
530 if (!Rflags.ZeroFlag)
531 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
532 else
533 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
534
535 break;
536
537 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JB:
538
539 //
540 // Jump if below (jb),
541 // Jump if not above or equal (jnae),
542 // Jump if carry (jc)
543 //
544
545 //
546 // This jump is unsigned
547 //
548
549 if (Rflags.CarryFlag)
550 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
551 else
552 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
553
554 break;
555
556 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNB:
557
558 //
559 // Jump if not below (jnb),
560 // Jump if above or equal (jae),
561 // Jump if not carry (jnc)
562 //
563
564 //
565 // This jump is unsigned
566 //
567
568 if (!Rflags.CarryFlag)
569 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
570 else
571 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
572
573 break;
574
575 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JBE:
576
577 //
578 // Jump if below or equal (jbe),
579 // Jump if not above (jna)
580 //
581
582 //
583 // This jump is unsigned
584 //
585
586 if (Rflags.CarryFlag || Rflags.ZeroFlag)
587 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
588 else
589 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
590
591 break;
592
593 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNBE:
594
595 //
596 // Jump if above (ja),
597 // Jump if not below or equal (jnbe)
598 //
599
600 //
601 // This jump is unsigned
602 //
603
604 if (!Rflags.CarryFlag && !Rflags.ZeroFlag)
605 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
606 else
607 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
608
609 break;
610
611 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JL:
612
613 //
614 // Jump if less (jl),
615 // Jump if not greater or equal (jnge)
616 //
617
618 //
619 // This jump is signed
620 //
621
622 if (Rflags.SignFlag != Rflags.OverflowFlag)
623 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
624 else
625 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
626
627 break;
628
629 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNL:
630
631 //
632 // Jump if greater or equal (jge),
633 // Jump if not less (jnl)
634 //
635
636 //
637 // This jump is signed
638 //
639
640 if (Rflags.SignFlag == Rflags.OverflowFlag)
641 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
642 else
643 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
644
645 break;
646
647 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JLE:
648
649 //
650 // Jump if less or equal (jle),
651 // Jump if not greater (jng)
652 //
653
654 //
655 // This jump is signed
656 //
657
658 if (Rflags.ZeroFlag || Rflags.SignFlag != Rflags.OverflowFlag)
659 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
660 else
661 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
662
663 break;
664
665 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNLE:
666
667 //
668 // Jump if greater (jg),
669 // Jump if not less or equal (jnle)
670 //
671
672 //
673 // This jump is signed
674 //
675
676 if (!Rflags.ZeroFlag && Rflags.SignFlag == Rflags.OverflowFlag)
677 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
678 else
679 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
680
681 break;
682
683 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JP:
684
685 //
686 // Jump if parity (jp),
687 // Jump if parity even (jpe)
688 //
689
690 if (Rflags.ParityFlag)
691 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
692 else
693 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
694
695 break;
696
697 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNP:
698
699 //
700 // Jump if not parity (jnp),
701 // Jump if parity odd (jpo)
702 //
703
704 if (!Rflags.ParityFlag)
705 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
706 else
707 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
708
709 break;
710
711 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JCXZ:
712 case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JECXZ:
713
714 //
715 // Jump if %CX register is 0 (jcxz),
716 // Jump if% ECX register is 0 (jecxz)
717 //
718
719 //
720 // Actually this instruction are rarely used
721 // but if we want to support these instructions then we
722 // should read ecx and cx each time in the debuggee,
723 // so it's better to just ignore it as a non-conditional
724 // jump
725 //
726 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_NOT_CONDITIONAL_JUMP;
727
728 default:
729
730 //
731 // It's not a jump
732 //
733 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_NOT_CONDITIONAL_JUMP;
734 break;
735 }
736
737 return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_ERROR;
738 }
739}

@ DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN

@ DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN

◆ SeparateTo64BitValue()

string SeparateTo64BitValue ( UINT64  Value)

add ` between 64 bit values and convert them to string

Parameters
Value
Returns
string
28{
29 ostringstream OstringStream;
30 string Temp;
31
32 OstringStream << setw(16) << setfill('0') << hex << Value;

◆ ShowMemoryCommandDB()

void ShowMemoryCommandDB ( unsigned char *  OutputBuffer,
UINT  Size,
UINT64  Address,
DEBUGGER_READ_MEMORY_TYPE  MemoryType,
UINT64  Length 
)

Show memory in bytes (DB)

Parameters
OutputBufferthe buffer to show
Sizesize of memory to read
Addresslocation of where to read the memory
MemoryTypetype of memory (phyical or virtual)
LengthLength of memory to show
182{
183 unsigned int Character;
184
185 for (int i = 0; i < Size; i += 16)
186 {
187 if (MemoryType == DEBUGGER_READ_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS)
188 {
189 ShowMessages("#\t");
190 }
191
192 //
193 // Print address
194 //
195 ShowMessages("%s ", SeparateTo64BitValue((UINT64)(Address + i)).c_str());
196
197 //
198 // Print the hex code
199 //
200 for (size_t j = 0; j < 16; j++)
201 {
202 //
203 // check to see if the address is valid or not
204 //
205 if (i + j >= Length)
206 {
207 ShowMessages("?? ");
208 }
209 else
210 {
211 ShowMessages("%02X ", OutputBuffer[i + j]);
212 }
213 }
214
215 //
216 // Print the character
217 //
218 ShowMessages(" ");
219 for (size_t j = 0; j < 16; j++)
220 {
221 Character = (OutputBuffer[i + j]);
222 if (isprint(Character))
223 {
224 ShowMessages("%c", Character);
225 }
226 else
227 {
228 ShowMessages(".");
229 }
230 }
231
232 //
233 // Go to new line
234 //
235 ShowMessages("\n");
236 }
237}

78 // vsprintf_s and vswprintf_s return the number of characters written,

◆ g_DeviceHandle

HANDLE g_DeviceHandle
extern

Holds the global handle of device which is used to send the request to the kernel by IOCTL, this handle is not used for IRP Pending of message tracing this handle is used in KD VMM.
